name: #ExtinctHominids – Aunt Australopithecus * fungi edition *
description:
* Special fungi edition for early collectors *

Australopithecus Africanus. South Africa. Middle Pliocene to Early Pleistocene. Extinct. 

Early hominins like the Australopithecus were omnivores that often relied on foraging on forest floors, finding all sorts of morsels like mushrooms.  

They shared the earth with cousins Australophiticus Afarensis, Homo Habilis, Homo Rudolfensis, Paranthropus Robustus, and others.
